      • isNullThen

        public static void isNullThen(java.lang.Object $receiver,
                              kotlin.jvm.functions.Function0<kotlin.Unit> callback)

        Calls the specified function block whenever this is null.

        Note that if this is chained after a AnyKt.isNotNullThen block where that AnyKt.isNotNullThen assigns a null valueto this then AnyKt.isNullThen block will be called since this is now null, so chaining can lead to unexpected behavior. This is not meant for a replacement of an if...then clause, but as a shortcut method to evaluate if this is null.

        See Also:
        AnyKt.isNotNullThen, AnyKt.isNotNullThen, AnyKt.isNullThen

      • isNotNullThen

        public static <T> void isNotNullThen(T $receiver,
                                     kotlin.jvm.functions.Function1<? super T,kotlin.Unit> callback)

        Calls the specified function block with this value as its argument whenever this is not null and returns Unit.

        Note that if this is chained after a AnyKt.isNullThen block where that AnyKt.isNullThen block assigns value to T then AnyKt.isNotNullThenblock will be called since T is no longer null, so chaining can lead to unexpected behavior. This is not meant for a replacement of an if...then clause, but as a shortcut method to evaluate if T is not null.

        See Also:
        AnyKt.isNullThen, AnyKt.isNullThen, AnyKt.isNotNullThen
